-- Australia's NAB sells $1 bln UK property loan portfolio
-- By Sonali Paul
-- Sun Jul 27, 2014 06:55PM EDT
-- None



MELBOURNE, July 28 (Reuters) - National Australia Bank Ltd <NAB.AX> has agreed to sell a 625 million pound ($1.06 billion) portfolio of mostly non-performing UK commercial property loans to private equity firm Cerberus Global Investors.

NAB said on Monday the sale would generate a small gain on net book value would release about 127 million pounds in capital for the group, which owns the Clydesdale and Yorkshire Banks in the United Kingdom. The UK business has been a drag on the Australian company's earnings for many years.